orset/IMG_2642.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/IMG_2644.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/IMG_2644.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>Features:</strong></p><ul><li>Front busk corset;</li><li>A corset for a teenager body proportions;</li><li>Tiered skirt with ruffles.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills you gain:</strong></p><ul><li>How to sew a teens corset with a steel busk;</li><li>How to customize a standard corset pattern to make it suitable for a teenage girl;</li><li>How to&nbsp;make a perfect skirt with many ruffles;</li><li>Original corset decorations.</li></ul><p><strong>Where to use:</strong></p><ul><li>An exclusive fancy dress for&nbsp;your teenage child;</li><li>Perfect solution for proms, celebrations, costume parties and other special events.</li></ul><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;4h 23m</p></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-12-sewing-boning-tunnels/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-12-sewing-boning-tunnels/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-08-08T20:50:59+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-08-08T20:50:59+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 12. Sewing Boning Tunnels."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 12. Sewing Boning Tunnels."><meta itemprop="description" content="Now I need to pin all princess seams of the corset, finish the slits, and sew tunnels for inserting plastic bones. To make sure everything is pinned evenly"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Corset with a Front Busk for 15 Years Old Girl"><meta itemprop="keywords" content="corset with a front busk for 15 years old girl, video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 12. Sewing Boning Tunnels.</h1><p><strong>Now I need to pin all princess seams of the corset, finish the slits, and sew tunnels for inserting plastic bones.</strong> To make sure everything is pinned evenly, I insert a pin in the groove of the princess seam and check where it comes out at the back. It is supposed to come out from the groove as well.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I start by putting pins in the fabric at rather large intervals and then I add more pins in-between to secure it more properly. </strong>The princess seams of the face and the lining may be a little misaligned at the cup level. This is not a mistake. As you remember, the fabric was eased in to give the cups their proper shape. As the result, the seams may become misaligned. Just make sure the face fabric is even and carefully re-distribute it if needed. When you go below that area though, try your best to get the pin in the groove of the princess seam both on the face and on the lining.</p><p><strong>I carefully align the seams at the bottom. </strong></p><p>Then, I pin the face with the lining in the slit area carefully aligning the edges of the slit and especially the top points.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Pin the pieces together along the bottom edge to spread the face fabric vertically as well. </strong>There will be no tunnel along the bust princess seam so I don't have to pin it.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>This is what the pinning looks like from the inside. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I do the same with the other half of the corset. </strong></p><p><strong>And then, I sew right in the groove of each princess seam. </strong></p><p><strong>I sew along the back princess seam. </strong>I try not to sew over the pins but remove them gradually as I sew.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I make a parallel row of stitches to form a tunnel. </strong>I believe 1.2cm is a perfect width so I sew 1.2cm from the princess seam. I insert a plastic bone in the tunnel just to test it and examine the princess seam. It looks very good so I will stick to the same width in further work.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Next, I sew in the groove of the side seam. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>The tunnel is purposely made left of the seam to make the bone get on the front of the corset. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew in the groove of the side princess seam of the front.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I reach the slit and continue sewing along just 1mm from its left edge.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image021.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>And then, I make another parallel row of stitches in the groove of the side princess seam, 1mm from the first row.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image023.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I move to the other side of the slit and continue sewing along the very edge.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image025.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I form a tunnel right of the princess seam.</strong> I check whether the bone fits in well and looks neat. Perfect!</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image027.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image029.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew a tunnel right of the princess seam, i.e. from the other side of the slit.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image031.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I have formed the tunnels and finished the slit.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%2012.files/image033.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>The same things need to be done with the other half of the corset.&nbsp; </strong></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format.</p><p>To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose “<strong>PRINT IN ACTUAL SIZE</strong>“.</p><p>In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printer.</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/patterns/FrontBuskCorset.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Front Busk Corset Pattern</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>
 
